WendzelNNTPd was originally written by Steffen Wendzel (since 2004) who is
also the maintainer of this project.
   mail: steffen (at) wendzel (dot) de | web: https://www.wendzel.de

If you contributed to the project but are not mentioned below: please drop
me an e-mail and I will be happy to add you! :)

Major Contributors (in chronological order):

14. Ole Ludwig (FernUniversität in Hagen, 2025):
     - autotools (configure) replacement of original configure script
     - several bugfixes
     - sighandler improvement
     - several code cleanups
     - packaging support
     - transforming the LaTeX docs into markdown + making it web-based
     - extended Docker support for production images
     - systemd service
     - additional packages (especially Debian and integration into
       openSUSE build service)
     - revised/extended the set of manpages
     - ... and several more enhancements, cf. CHANGELOG!
13. Sven Liebert (FernUniversität in Hagen, 2024):
     - Docker support for development purposes
     - improved signal handling
12. Christian Barthel (2023):
     - Postgres support (currently experimental) and code clean-up
11. Michael Baeuerle (since 2023):
     - provision of NetBSD port to pkgsrc
     - provision of multiple patches
8-10.Sven Liebert,
     Michael Dunsky, and
     Christoph Grill (all FernUniversität in Hagen, 2022-2024):
     - TLS/NTTPS/SNNTP support
 7. @deavmi (2018-2019):
     - code clean-up and documentation fixes
 6. @pintman (2015):
     - motivated configurable posting size limit (feature request)
 5. @rk (2012):
     - reported multiple bugs
 4. Ann Lynnworth (2009-2015)
     - bug reporting, testing, enduser feedback, helped improving documentation
 3. Nils Dabrock (2009):
     - bug report
 2. Kristijan Smiljanic (2008):
     - contributed PHP-based database converter script for the 1.3.0-release
 1. killerfox (2005):
     - early tests of v. 0.1.4-beta under Solaris and Linux

